    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Smooth-grained, natural- or cream-colored calf, vegetable-tanned, usually with bark, and commonly used in the 19th and early 20th centuries in binding law books, particularly in England. It has been superceded for that use by "law buckram."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
